# 📌 Chapter Summary

In this chapter, you learned that traditional Java development becomes increasingly difficult as applications grow. Manual object creation, tight coupling, scattered configuration, and repetitive infrastructure code make enterprise applications harder to maintain and test.

Spring addresses these issues by taking responsibility for object creation, dependency management, and application infrastructure, allowing developers to focus on business logic.

